OL,6,FThen, through 2022 and 2023,
OL,7,Fskyrocketing inflation caused their
OL,8,Foperating costs to rise, while the
OL,9,Fcost-of-living crisis depressed sales.
OL,11,FThe industry has long called for
OL,12,Freforms to business rates as a means
OL,13,Fof tackling the issue.
OL,15,FPubs currently have a 75% discount on
OL,16,Fthe tax, but this is set to end in
OL,17,FMarch 2025.
OL,19,FPubs currently make an average of 12p
OL,20,Fprofit on every pint of beer once
OL,21,Ftaxes and costs have been deducted.
